<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="582" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,152,683]" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,297,153,179]" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">Remark</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dubatolov, V. V. &amp; Kishida, Y. &amp; Wang, M." box="[312,594,152,179]" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" pagination="103 - 106" refId="ref6535" refString="Dubatolov, V. V., Kishida, Y. &amp; Wang, M. (2012 b) Two new species sibling to Ghoria albocinerea Moore from South China (Lepidoptera, Arctiidae: Lithosiinae). Tinea, 22 (2), 103 - 106." type="journal article" year="2012">
Dubatolov 
<emphasis box="[439,497,152,178]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">et al.</emphasis>
(2012b)
</bibRefCitation>
did not illustrate the vesica structure of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dubatolov, Kishida &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2012" box="[1055,1221,152,179]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Ghoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinotibetica">
<emphasis box="[1055,1221,152,179]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">G. sinotibetica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, we dissected a few of topotypical males (collected in the same gorge as the type series) and all of them have the constant valva shape, the aedeagus size as well as the size and shape of spines in aedeagus vesica (
<figureCitation box="[1165,1294,224,251]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–27" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1765,1790]" captionTargetBox="[183,1407,191,1734]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[176,1411,181,1740]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 24–27. Ghoria spp., male genitalia. Depositories of specimens: 24, 25, 27 – MWM/ZSM; 26 – SZMN (photo by V.V. Dubatolov)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887630/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">Figs 24, 25</figureCitation>
) identical to those of the 
<typeStatus box="[289,387,260,286]" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[402,487,260,287]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–27" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1765,1790]" captionTargetBox="[183,1407,191,1734]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[176,1411,181,1740]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 24–27. Ghoria spp., male genitalia. Depositories of specimens: 24, 25, 27 – MWM/ZSM; 26 – SZMN (photo by V.V. Dubatolov)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887630/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="582" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,152,683]" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,312,296,323]" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Forewing length is 
<quantity box="[532,649,297,323]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" unit="mm" value="17.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="17.0">17–18 mm</quantity>
in males (17.5 mm in the 
<typeStatus box="[928,1025,296,323]" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">holotype</typeStatus>
) and 18.5 mm in females. The species (
<figureCitation box="[159,280,332,359]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1904,1929]" captionTargetBox="[170,1420,185,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[161,1426,181,1878]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Ghoria spp., adults. Specimens are deposited in MWM/ZSM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887624" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887624/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">Figs 11, 12</figureCitation>
) is similar externally to 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Černý, 2020" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2020" box="[542,664,332,359]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Ghoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mubupa" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[542,664,332,359]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">G. mubupa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[669,729,333,359]" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[669,729,333,359]" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[743,866,332,359]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1904,1929]" captionTargetBox="[170,1420,185,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[161,1426,181,1878]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Ghoria spp., adults. Specimens are deposited in MWM/ZSM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887624" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887624/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">Figs 13, 14</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Černý, 2020" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2020" box="[926,1042,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Ghoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="synnefo" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[926,1042,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">G. synnefo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1048,1108,333,359]" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1048,1108,333,359]" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1122,1246,332,359]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1904,1929]" captionTargetBox="[170,1420,185,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[161,1426,181,1878]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Ghoria spp., adults. Specimens are deposited in MWM/ZSM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887624" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887624/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">Figs 15, 16</figureCitation>
), but differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Černý, 2020" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2020" box="[151,274,368,395]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Ghoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mubupa" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[151,274,368,395]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">G. mubupa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[280,341,369,395]" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[280,341,369,395]" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by its slightly paler male hindwing and monotonous dark grey female hindwing (that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Černý, 2020" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2020" box="[1314,1436,368,395]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Ghoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mubupa" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1314,1436,368,395]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">G. mubupa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,212,405,431]" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,212,405,431]" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is whitish) and from 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Černý, 2020" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2020" box="[445,563,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Ghoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="synnefo" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[445,563,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">G. synnefo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[569,629,405,431]" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[569,629,405,431]" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by its slightly smaller size and pale yellow edge of forewing costa (that is bright yellow in 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Černý, 2020" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2020" box="[334,452,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Ghoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="synnefo" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[334,452,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">G. synnefo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[459,520,441,467]" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[459,520,441,467]" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
). The male genital capsule of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dubatolov, Kishida &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2012" box="[855,1017,440,467]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Ghoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinotibetica">
<emphasis box="[855,1017,440,467]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">G. sinotibetica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1031,1158,440,467]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–27" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1765,1790]" captionTargetBox="[183,1407,191,1734]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[176,1411,181,1740]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 24–27. Ghoria spp., male genitalia. Depositories of specimens: 24, 25, 27 – MWM/ZSM; 26 – SZMN (photo by V.V. Dubatolov)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887630/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">Figs 24–26</figureCitation>
) is very similar to that of the externally dissimilar 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2020" box="[422,580,476,503]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Ghoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longivesica">
<emphasis box="[422,580,476,503]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">G. longivesica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[594,720,476,503]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–23" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1884,1909]" captionTargetBox="[155,1435,185,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1435,181,1858]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 20–23. Ghoria spp., male genitalia. Specimens are deposited in MWM/ZSM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887628/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">Figs 22, 23</figureCitation>
), but the aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dubatolov, Kishida &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2012" box="[958,1120,476,503]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Ghoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinotibetica">
<emphasis box="[958,1120,476,503]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">G. sinotibetica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is conspicuously shorter and narrower, the vesica is ca. 2.5 times shorter than that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2020" box="[757,915,512,539]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Ghoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longivesica">
<emphasis box="[757,915,512,539]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">G. longivesica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and lacks a subbasal diverticulum, the subbasal chamber of vesica is shorter and bearing the broader field of small cornuti, and the distal diverticulum bears conspicuously smaller spines. The female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dubatolov, Kishida &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2012" box="[643,804,584,611]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Ghoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinotibetica">
<emphasis box="[643,804,584,611]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">G. sinotibetica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[817,900,584,611]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–36" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1829,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,182,1799]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1435,181,1803]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 32–36. Ghoria spp., female genitalia. Specimens are deposited in MWM/ZSM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887634" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887634/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">Figs 35</figureCitation>
) differ clearly from those of other related species (
<figureCitation box="[159,366,620,647]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 32–36" captionStart-1="FIGURES 37–38" captionStartId-0="11.[151,264,1829,1854]" captionStartId-1="12.[151,264,1436,1461]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1431,182,1799]" captionTargetBox-1="[200,1381,675,1405]" captionTargetId-0="figure@11.[151,1435,181,1803]" captionTargetId-1="figure@12.[197,1389,669,1411]" captionTargetPageId-0="11" captionTargetPageId-1="12" captionText-0="FIGURES 32–36. Ghoria spp., female genitalia. Specimens are deposited in MWM/ZSM." captionText-1="FIGURES 37–38. Ghoria spp., female genitalia. Specimens are deposited in MWM/ZSM." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887634" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887636" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3887634/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3887636/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">Figs 32–34, 36–38</figureCitation>
) by the very short ductus bursae and the left-positioned signum bursae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1184,656,683]" pageId="7" pageNumber="582" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,152,683]" box="[199,1184,656,683]" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,656,683]" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">Distribution</emphasis>
. The species is known from northwestern 
<collectingRegion box="[821,1018,656,682]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">Sichuan Province</collectingRegion>
of 
<collectingCountry box="[1055,1122,656,682]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="582">China</collectingCountry>
only.
</paragraph>
